Engineers and Scientists at Medtronic create our market-leading portfolio of innovations. Medtronicâ€™s corporate research group within the Corporate Strategic Scientific Operations division provides scientific and technical support and consultation services across the global Medtronic Enterprise. 
 We have an exciting opportunity for a Senior Scientist who is eager to work on Physiological Modeling and other multi-disciplinary challenges where they can leverage their expertise in human physiology, clinical physiology, anatomy, biomechanics, cardiovascular and pulmonary physiology, endocrinology, and the pathophysiology of chronic diseases. The role will work under limited supervision as part of a diverse team of experts spanning a variety of scientific and engineering disciplines. 
 A Day in the Life: 
 Work collaboratively with Medtronic Business Units to solve technical problems Apply advanced technical principles, theories, and concepts and develop innovative solutions using computational models Implement principles of physiology to drive research and development Utilize physiological modeling tools to inform the design and development of new test methods, equipment, materials, and processes Use principles of physiology to assist in the design and evaluation of new and existing medical devices Perform model verification and validation assessments as appropriate Support senior technical staff within the Core Technologies group Share experience and knowledge with Medtronic Business units Provide regular status updates to internal customers and management Communicate technical assessments and analyses via written technical documents and oral presentations 
 
 Must Have: Minimum Requirements 
 Bachelors degree required 
 Minimum of 4 years of relevant experience, or advanced degree with a minimum of 2 years relevant experience 
 
 Nice to Have: 
 PhD -or- MS with 3+ years of experience -or- BS with 5+ years of experience. Degree should be in Integrative Physiology, Exercise Physiology, Anatomy & Physiology, Applied Mathematics or closely related fields Record of research and scholarship in systems biology, physiological modeling, or closely related field Strong background in mathematical physiology and numerical implementation of physiological models Strong background in the pathophysiology of chronic disease Strong scripting and programing skills Flexibility in working hours to accommodate collaboration across geographies Experience with simulation using finite element methods or computational fluid dynamics Experience with Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and Deep Learning networks Application of techniques such as: Reinforcement Learning, Transferred Learning, Computer Vision, Image Segmentation, and PCA Experience in working across Windows and Linux operating systems 
